INSERT INTO `ed_chapter` VALUES (1,2,'22','222','https://amtil-cms.s3.amazonaws.com/88d0e479ae1ea376c85a1624409b36a0',222,'222','222'),(2,1,'Aircraft Drawings','In this Chapter you will be learning the different views and drawing techniques used by aircraft engineers and mechanics. This will include types of drawings, methods of illustration, lines and their meanings, symbols, standards, and drawing sketches.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',1,'TBD',NULL),(3,1,'Physics','In this course you will be learning the different physics principles in aviation. These include energy, stress, motion, mechanical advantage, the atmosphere, sound, and many more.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',1,'TBD',NULL),(4,1,'Aircraft Weight and Balance','The weight of an aircraft and its balance are extremely important for the operation of an aircraft in a safe and efficient manner. In this chapter you will learn procedures for weighing an aircraft, how to prepare an aircraft for weighing, loading an aircraft for flight, and the proper use of ballasts.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',1,'TBD',NULL),(5,1,'Aircraft Materials, Processes, & Hardware','This chapter includes the different methods, techniques, and materials involved in maintaining airframe and powerplant structures. These include aircraft metals, the metalworking processes, heat treatment, non metallic aircraft materials, and hardware.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',1,'TBD',NULL),(6,1,'Aircraft Cleaning & Corrosion Control ','Many aircraft structures are made of metal, and the most insidious form of damage to those structures is corrosion. In this chapter you will learn corrosion control, forms of corrosion, corrosion removal, aircraft cleaning, and powerplant cleaning.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',1,'TBD',NULL),(7,1,'Fluid Lines & Fittings','Fluid lines and fittings are used to transfer different fluids to aircraft components and engines. IN this chapter you will learn about rigid fluid lines, flexible hose fluid lines, and different types of fittings.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',1,'TBD',NULL),(8,1,'Inspection Fundamentals','Inspections are visual examinations and manual checks to determine the condition of an aircraft or component. In this chapter you will learn basic inspection techniques, special inspections, and routine inspections.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',1,'TBD',NULL),(9,1,'Hand Tools and Measuring Devices','The aviation maintenance technician spends a major portion of each day using a wide variety of hand tools to accomplish maintenance tasks. In this chapter you will learn about general purpose tools, metal cutting tools, and layout and measuring tools.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',1,'TBD',NULL),(10,1,'Basic Electricity ','This subject addresses the fundamental concepts that are the building blocks for advanced electrical knowledge and practical troubleshooting. In this chapter you will learn about static electricity, power and energy, circuit protection devices, basic circuit analysis and troubleshooting, and more.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',1,'TBD',NULL),(11,1,'Safety, Ground Operations, & Servicing ','In this chapter you will learn about shop safety, flight line safety, tiedown procedures, ground movement of aircraft, and fuel servicing of aircraft.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',1,'TBD',NULL),(12,1,'Publications, Forms, & Records','In this chapter, you will learn about the different aspects of title 14 Code of Federal Regulations (14CFR) and the documentations used in enhancing it. These include;airworthiness standards, airworthiness directives, flight rules, records and the policiies that govern aircarft safety.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',1,'TBD',NULL),(13,1,'The Mechanic Certificate','This chapter addresses the pathways, guidlines and requirements needed to obtain mechanical certification and inspection authorization.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',1,'TBD',NULL);
