INSERT INTO `ed_lesson` VALUES (1,1,1,1,'Fractions','Fractions: In this lesson- we will be covering the contrast between whole numbers fractions and why they are important. We will also be covering the steps on how to add- subtract- multiply and divide fractions','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',5,NULL),(2,2,1,1,'Mixed Numbers','Mixed Numbers: Mixed numbers are a combination of fractions and whole numbers. In this lesson- we will be covering the different techniques used in adding and subtracting these types of numbers.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',5,NULL),(3,3,1,1,'The Decimal Number System ','The Decimal Number System: In this lesson- we will be reviewing the standard number system and how it relates to decimal points. We will also be looking at techniques used in adding- subtracting- multiplying- and dividing decimal points.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',5,NULL),(4,4,1,1,'Ratios','Ratios: A basic numerical way of comparing different numbers or quantities. We will be covering how ratios are used in aviation to solve problems.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',5,NULL),(5,5,1,1,'Proportions ','Proportions: Proportion reviews equality statements used in establishing rations. In this lesson- we will be reviewing various proportion examples and how they apply to aviation.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',5,NULL),(6,6,1,1,'Percentages','Percentages: In this lesson- we will be covering the basic understanding of percentages and how they can be expressed as decimal numbers- fractions- and whole numbers.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',5,NULL),(7,7,1,1,'Positive and Negative Numbers (Signed Numbers)','Positive and Negative Numbers (Signed Numbers): In this lesson- we will be covering the effects of signs on numbers. We will be reviewing the effects of different signs on the quantity- size- or interpretation of the number.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',5,NULL),(8,8,1,1,'Powers','Powers: Also known as exponents- is a unique way of representing numbers that are multiplied by themselves. We will be covering squared numbers- cubed numbers- negative powers- and zero powers.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',5,NULL),(9,9,1,1,'Scientific Notation ','Scientific Notation: Scientific notations are also known as powers of 10\"\" are mainly used to scale aircraft drawings to readable sizes. In this lesson- we will be looking at how they can be altered.\"\"','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',5,NULL),(10,10,1,1,'Algebra','Algebra: While mathematics mainly focuses on numbers- algebra is a portion of mathematics that deals with numbers- symbols- variables- and equations.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',5,NULL),(11,11,1,1,'Computing Area of Two-Dimensional Solids','Computing Area of Two-Dimensional Solids: In this lesson- we will be reviewing how to calculate the amount of surface on a shape or object which include- rectangles- circle- squares- etc. These types of objects are known as 2-dimensional objects.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',5,NULL),(12,12,1,1,'Computing Volume of Three-Dimensional Solids','Computing Volume of Three-Dimensional Solids: In this lesson- we will be exploring variables like length- width- height needed in calculating the total volume for these types of objects.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',5,NULL),(13,13,1,1,'Computing Surface Area of Three-Dimensional Solids','Computing Surface Area of Three-Dimensional Solids: Three-dimensional solids have more than one surface. In this lesson- we will be covering the methods used in determining the total surface area for these types of objects and their differences. ','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',5,NULL),(14,14,1,1,'Trigonometric Functions','Trigonometric Functions: In this lesson- we will understand the different angles and sides of a triangle. We will cover the methods used in measuring them and the formula for calculating each side.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',5,NULL),(15,15,1,1,'Measurement Systems','Measurement Systems: Outside the US measuring system- there are other internationally recognized standard measuring techniques used across the globe. In this lesson- we will be exploring what these measuring systems are and how they relate to each other.','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',5,NULL),(16,16,1,1,'The Binary Number System ','The Binary Number System: This number system only has two digits 0 and 1\"\" which can be used to represent a lot of situations. In this lesson- we will be exploring how binary systems are used in switches- valves and their relationship with the different types of gates.\"\"','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',5,NULL),(17,1,2,1,'Basics','Basics','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',6,NULL),(18,2,2,1,'Types of Drawings','Types of Drawings','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',7,NULL),(19,3,2,1,'Title Blocks','Title Blocks','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',8,NULL),(20,4,2,1,'Other Drawing Data','Other Drawing Data','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',9,NULL),(21,5,2,1,'Methods of Illustration','Methods of Illustration','https://amtil-mvp.s3.amazonaws.com/images/User+Interface+Images/NoImg.jpg',10,NULL),(22,6,2,1,'Lines and Thier Meanings','Lines and Thier M